@Quar:  I hope your little girl feels all better really soon.  Sending good thoughts her way.<br>
<br>
In other news, I agree about AngryPidgeon.  I'm not convinced that Yos is scum, but if one of Yos-GC HAS to be scum (something I don't buy into, either) then I would say it's Yos and not GC.

@Pegasus:  You are mainly commenting on the current wagons and on Empire.  You commented on AngryPidgeon and supported that wagon; same with Quaroath and Quilford.  I don't see a lot of input about anyone else.  Do you have any strong reads on anyone else in the game?  <br>
<br>
It feels a bit to me like you're trying to push or influence wagons already in existence without widening your focus at all.  Do you think that's a fair assessment?

EBWOP:  I just realised I didn't address one part of my post correctly (it's early for me, sorry).  This part should have been @Quaroath:<br>
<br>
@Quaroath:  Since you think I am scum, why do you rule out an SK-Bookitty pairing?  Let's assume for a moment that I have been lynched already and flipped town; that would leave SK as a great target for you, right?  Why do you think he's scum specifically?

@Peg: really?  If you think I'm scum with Yos then vote me.<br>
<br>
I'm p annoyed that you think I'm scum for defending 2 popular lynches today.

I'd be down for a Zito lynch, but we can do Chamber first today.<br>
<br>
